HEADWORD: Self-existence
<hw>Self`-ex*ist"ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Inherent
existence; existence possessed by virtue of a being's own nature, and
independent of any other being or cause; -- an attribute peculiar to
God.</def> <rj><au>Blackmore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-existent</ent>⟦br⟧
